k president is set forth in the Federal Reserve Act.";i:2;s:202:"Subject to the approval of the Federal Reserve Board of Governors the president is appointed by the Reserve Banks Class B and C directors those directors who are not affiliated with a supervised entity.";i:3;s:75:"Who are the members of the Federal Reserve Board and how are they selected.";i:4;s:114:"The members of the Board of Governors are nominated by the President of the United States and confirmed by the US.";i:5;s:186:"By law the appointments must yield a fair representation of the financial agricultural industrial and commercial interests and geographical divisions of the country and no two Governors.";i:6;s:225:"Under authority provided by the Banking Act of 1935 the president of the United States appoints the seven members of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System who are confirmed by the Senate and serve for 14 years.";i:7;s:12:"Log in here.";i:8;s:93:"The Chairman of the Federal Reserve Board is appointed by the President of the United States.";i:9;s:46:"The President gets to nominate a candidate to.";i:10;s:101:"The chairman of the Federal Reserve is selected by the President from among the members of the board.";i:11;s:49:"That person must then be confirmed by the Senate.";i:12;s:42:"The term for the chairman is only 4 years.";i:13;s:106:"The chair and each of the governors of the fed are nominated by the President and confirmed by the Senate.";i:14;s:28:"She serves a four year term.";i:15;s:38:"Janet Yellins term ends in early 2018.";i:16;s:106:"The board of governors of the Fed have 14 year terms to reduce the opportunity for political appointments.";i:17;s:104:"On November 2 2017 President Donald Trump nominated Powell to serve as the chair of the Federal Reserve.";i:18;s:160:"On December 5 the Senate Banking Committee approved Powells nomination to be Chair in a 221 vote with Senator Elizabeth Warren casting the lone dissenting vote.";i:19;s:138:"The members of the Board 